name: r-ggprism
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggprism
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggprism_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggprism/ggprism_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 57324fcd31c084cc11fedb63ba399aa76ec1a4e23a9bb95a89c1e8925106b025

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.2.0
    - r-glue
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.2.0
    - r-glue
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggprism')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggprism')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://csdaw.github.io/ggprism/, https://github.com/csdaw/ggprism
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  summary: Provides various themes, palettes, and other functions that are used to customise
    ggplots to look like they were made in 'GraphPad Prism'. The 'Prism'-look is achieved
    with theme_prism() and scale_fill|colour_prism(), axes can be changed with custom
    guides like guide_prism_minor(), and significance indicators added with add_pvalue().
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: ggprism
# Title: A 'ggplot2' Extension Inspired by 'GraphPad Prism'

The 'Prism'-look is achieved with theme_prism() and scale_fill|colour_prism(), axes can be changed with custom guides like guide_prism_minor(), and significance indicators added with add_pvalue().
